\b\f39\fs22\insrsid94135\charrsid8210080 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid94135\charrsid8210080 First of all, could you tell me, or do you wish to tell me, when you were born?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid7229103 Sandra:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid94135\charrsid8210080 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid94135\charrsid8210080 
(LAUGHS) Well, I guess you can find it out anyway!  I was born in 1934.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid7229103 Elaine:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid94135\charrsid8210080 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid94135\charrsid8210080 And where?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid7229103 Sandra:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid94135\charrsid8210080 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid94135\charrsid8210080 
In London.  In Barnes, actually.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid7229103 Elaine:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid94135\charrsid8210080 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid94135\charrsid8210080 And could you give me a 
bit of background on your family?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid7229103 Sandra:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid94135\charrsid8210080 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid94135\charrsid8210080 
Yeah.  My father was a proper doctor, he was a medical doctor, and a Jew. My mother was not particularly, not formally educated, but an antique dealer, and certainly not Jewish, but also not anything really, not p
ractising anything.  In fact, neither of them practised any religion, and they had agreed that we would be raised without benefit of membership to anything.  I have one brother who is 16 months older than I am, and a half-brother who is, I think, probably
 by now, dead, who was about 18 years older than I am.  Is that enough?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid7229103 Elaine:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid94135\charrsid8210080 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid94135\charrsid8210080 
And can you tell me what occupations your siblings went into?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid7229103 Sandra:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid94135\charrsid8210080 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid94135\charrsid8210080 
My brother did a degree in social science in South Africa, where we were at the time, but his vocation has been as an actor.  He\rquote s suffered a fair deal of mental illness, so he hasn\rquote 
t been as successful as he would wish, but he defines himself as an actor.  Oh, and the other one \endash  the half-brother \endash  was an architect in California.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid7229103 Elaine:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid94135\charrsid8210080 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid94135\charrsid8210080 So he lived in Cali
fornia and stayed there?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid7229103 Sandra:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid94135\charrsid8210080 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid94135\charrsid8210080 
Yeah.  Well, my mother lost touch with him between the ages of eight and - I don\rquote t know what it was - 38, something like that?  That\rquote s another story.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid7229103 Elaine:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid94135\charrsid8210080 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid94135\charrsid8210080 
Okay.  Now, about your early influences and so on, and what led you to university work, could you share some of that?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid7229103 Sandra:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid94135\charrsid8210080 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid94135\charrsid8210080 
We travelled a lot.  We were always in different places - I went to 17 schools before I matriculated - in Africa and in Canada, and a bit here.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid7229103 Elaine:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid94135\charrsid8210080 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid94135\charrsid8210080 This is your family?

\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid7229103 Sandra:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid94135\charrsid8210080 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid94135\charrsid8210080 Yeah.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid7229103 Elaine:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid94135\charrsid8210080 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid94135\charrsid8210080 Your parents?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid7229103 Sandra:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid94135\charrsid8210080 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid94135\charrsid8210080 
Yeah.  My parents moved round a lot, and my father became a big cheese in the Royal Army Medical Corps during the Second Great War, and so he was in Somalia and we went there.  My mother had taken us to Canada - that was the first Canada incarnation 
\endash  as evacuees.  And then after the War, we joined my father in Africa, in Somalia, and then that didn\rquote t last because he came out of the Army, and then England wasn\rquote t looking too good, so should they go to Canada?  And then they tol
d my father he\rquote d have to re-qualify, so he said he wasn\rquote t going to do that.  So then we went to South Africa, and that\rquote s where I finished school, and stayed until I left home, which was at the age of about 19, I think.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid7229103 Elaine:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid94135\charrsid8210080 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid94135\charrsid8210080 
And did your parents stay in South Africa?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid7229103 Sandra:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid94135\charrsid8210080 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid94135\charrsid8210080 
