\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid7229103 Elaine:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid94135\charrsid8210080 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid94135\charrsid8210080 
And what it meant for different people.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid7229103 Sandra:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid94135\charrsid8210080 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid94135\charrsid8210080 
And what it meant for different people.  But again, the interaction with those kids was useful, because whether the data were accurate or fantastic or \'85
 I mean, I expected the kinship diagrams to be written in the sand, because I was from the Firth School.
 I had all these ideas, and these models and things like that, whereas actually asking people about who their fathers were, was much more useful as an ice-breaker.  I mean, }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid6627570\charrsid8210080 it}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid6627570 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid6627570\charrsid8210080 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid94135\charrsid8210080 
 ice-breakers that you want, in a way.
