\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid7229103 Elaine:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid94135\charrsid8210080 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid94135\charrsid8210080 
And how did you deal with that?  I mean, obviously you had to make modifications to the models you learned from Firth, let\rquote s say.  
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid7229103 Sandra:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid94135\charrsid8210080 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid94135\charrsid8210080 Yeah.  Well, I don
\rquote t think it was a question of making modifications of the models so much as - how can I say?  A kind of bricolage, of all the ideas that you have from all the things you\rquote ve been taught \endash  are taught as packages \endash 
 and then when you get to the field, somehow the packages have to be turned into a framework, into a holistic thing.  So kinship would be one element, but I wasn\rquote t studying 
kinship as such, I was just in that vague kind of way interested in how come plans don\rquote t work?  I can\rquote t now entirely remember the reasoning that I went through, but I think it\rquote 
s that holistic thing which, which is what you need.  And when you first get there, if you\rquote re not astute \endash  and I guess I wasn\rquote t \endash 
 as I say, I expected the kinship diagram to work, I could draw it in the sand, and then everything would be clear.  When you first get there, perhaps you\rquote re taking each of the chapters of your training and saying, \'93Okay\'94
, kinship, and now let me look at economics, and now let me look at - because that\rquote s how monographs used to be written \endash  one on religion, one on economics, one on politics \endash 
 so you would be carrying this baggage eagerly into the field.  And then you get there, and there are people behaving all over the place, and they\rquote re not saying, \'93Well, now I\rquote m doing something economic\'94, or \'93Now I\rquote 
m doing something political\'94, they\rquote re just living a life, and yet our job is somehow to make sense of these people behaving all over the place.  I mean, you can\rquote t just say, \'93It\rquote s a mess.  It\rquote s chaotic\'94
, you know, that sort of post-modern thing I\rquote m not too keen on, actually.  
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid7229103 Elaine:}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \b\f39\fs22\insrsid94135\charrsid8210080 \tab }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid94135\charrsid8210080 So you wouldn\rquote 
t consider yourself part of this post-modernist anthropologist group who are into deconstructing?
