t remember when now, on the business of sexual infections, and a kind of Venn diagram\rquote ish thing, where the central bit were sexual infection and treatment seeking overlap - this is what the biomedics are looking at, they\rquote 
re looking, very specifically, at sexual infection and treatment options - whereas in real life, the woman is juggling with a whole set of family problems, identity problems, time problems, money problems, health problems. So there\rquote 
s a whole wider context which is not taken into account by the narrow focus on the infections and the treatment.  And on the other side, there\rquote s a whole medical/biomedical, context, which the woman as an individual who\rquote s infec
ted, is completely not aware of. That you\rquote ve got to get your rates down, and you\rquote ve got to get penicillin into this person every day for four months, or whatever it is.  So their whole context \endash  the medical personnel\rquote 
s context, which makes sense of this issue \endash  is completely different from the patient\rquote s context.  And I think, sometimes, when you spell tha}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid11738368 t out, people say, \'93Oh yeah!\'94  }
{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0\afs22 \ltrch\fcs0 \f39\fs22\insrsid94135\charrsid8210080 Again, communication.  Whether it\rquote s possible to communicate more than to say, \'93Well, look, this is a different animal\'94, for 
