ticular occasion where we all had to come back to his seminar from the field, and present our work, and this chap came back from the field and did a presentation which was really so weak, and so awful, and I, for one, and others as well, I\rquote 
m sure, just wanted the floor to open up and to fall through it!  And then at the end of his presentation, there was a dead silence for a minute, and Firth managed to find the one thing in his whole presentation which had some mileage in it.  \'93
