hly speaking, family, I suppose.  Best thing.  And having interesting work, and being allowed to do interesting work is very good.  The worst thing is not having enough time to do everything you want to do, perhaps.  The illness of people you love is bad.
  I think it\rquote s a silly question, to be honest!  So you can wipe that out if you want to. But I think if I look at my life as a whole, a kind of tapestry, life\rquote s rich tapestry and so forth, I think I\rquote 
